@startuml journey-end-to-end
' ============================================================
' User-Experience Flow: Target-State End-to-End Journey
'
' Product/UX-clarity altitude (not an API sequence). Columns are the
' human/behind-the-scenes roles; node fill marks shipped vs planned so the
' loop doubles as a gap map.
'
' Primary path is child-initiated (target state, WS-B; shipped). Rose-filled
' nodes, if any remain, are gaps not yet built; as of this update every step
' in this loop is shipped (see the "Now covered" note at the bottom).
'
' Source screens / decisions:
'   frontend/src/router.tsx                         (kid + guardian route trees;
'     DeviceAuthorizedRoute wraps the kid tree, AdultGate the adult tree, ADR-014)
'   frontend/src/landing/LandingPage.tsx             (device-state-aware two-door
'     landing: Kids door -> /kids if a valid grant exists, else guardian login)
'   frontend/src/auth/DeviceAuthorizedRoute.tsx, auth/AdultGate.tsx (ADR-014)
'   frontend/src/library/RequestStory.tsx            (child-initiated request,
'     WS-B; shipped -- see api/story_requests.py)
'   frontend/src/guardian/RequestsPage.tsx            (guardian/admin approve
'     or decline a child's request, WS-B; shipped)
'   Phase 4a mobile UI wireframe concept spec (PR #47, shipped; the source doc under
'     docs/superpowers/specs/ was retired as scratch output once its work merged)
'   docs/planning/adr/adr-005-mandatory-human-approval.md  (approval gate)
'   docs/planning/adr/adr-014-device-authorized-kid-access.md (device grant;
'     single kid-to-adult step-up boundary)
'   docs/architecture/diagrams/seq-generation.puml  (behind-the-scenes detail)
'   docs/architecture/diagrams/seq-offline.puml     (offline read + reconnect)
'   docs/architecture/diagrams/seq-reading-state.puml (sync reconciliation)
'   docs/architecture/diagrams/seq-device-grant.puml (device grant mint/verify/revoke)
' ============================================================

title Target-State End-to-End User Journey\n(child-initiated; rose = planned, not yet built)

skinparam defaultFontName "Roboto"
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam roundCorner 10
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #5a3e28
skinparam ArrowFontColor #5a3e28
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FFFDF8
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam ActivityBorderThickness 1
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #f8f3e8
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #8c6f56
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #F1E9D8
skinparam NoteBorderColor #c9b48f
skinparam swimlaneWidth same

' Swimlane column tints = who is acting (storybook palette, tokens.css)
|#F0D9B8|Child|
|#CDDCEC|Guardian|
|#C5D9CC|Admin|
|#E4E4E4|System|

' ============ Act 1: Guardian onboarding (once) ============
|Guardian|
start
if (Is this device already authorized?\n(ADR-014 device grant)) then (no -- cold entry\nor unauthorized device)
  :Sign in
  (email/password, Google,
  or Apple if enabled);
  note right: /guardian/login  •  shipped\nADR-014: conditional now -- only a cold entry\nor an unauthorized device reaches this step
  :Create each child's profile
  (name + preset avatar);
  note right: /guardian/profiles  •  shipped
  :Authorize this device
  (mint a 90-day, revocable
  device grant for the family);
  note right: ADR-014 -- one grant per shared device;\nafter this, the device needs no further\nguardian sign-in for the child to read
else (yes -- valid grant already on device)
endif

' ============ The repeating story loop ============
repeat :a new story is wanted;

' ---- Act 2: Request (child-initiated primary path) ----
|Child|
:Open the app, tap Kids door;
note right: /  (Landing)  •  shipped\nAn authorized device goes straight to /kids;\nDeviceAuthorizedRoute checks the grant locally,\nno guardian login and no Supabase round-trip
:Tap my avatar;
note right: /kids  (Profile Picker)  •  shipped
:Open my Library, tap
"Request a story" and
say what it's about;
note right: RequestStory on the library page  •  shipped
|Guardian|
:See my child's request
(screened text + flags),
approve or decline it;
note right: /guardian/requests  •  shipped\n(guardian-own-family or admin-global)\nADR-014: crossing UP into the adult subtree from\nkid mode re-demands the password (AdultGate,\nsingle kid-to-adult boundary); once warm, moving\nbetween guardian and admin pages is free

' ---- Act 3: Behind the scenes ----
|System|
:Write the story
(staged, with fallback);
note right: generation pipeline  •  shipped\ndetail: seq-generation
:Safety check
(flags risky passages);
note right: validator gate  •  shipped
|Guardian|
:"My Requests" shows
"Generating...";
note right: /guardian/intake  •  shipped

' ---- Act 4: Human approval gate (ADR-005) ----
|Admin|
repeat :take the top item;
  :Open the review queue
  (Flagged, then Ready,
  then Still processing);
  note right: /guardian  (Console)  •  shipped
  :Read the flagged passages,
  then the full story;
  note right: /guardian/review/:id  •  shipped
backward:Send back with a note
-> the story is rewritten;
repeat while (Safe for a child?) is (no) not (yes -> approve)
:Approve
(recorded human gate, ADR-005);

' ---- Act 5: Assign ----
|Guardian|
:Assign it to the child
("Assign more" to add siblings);
note right: intake / assign  •  shipped
|Child|
:My avatar shows
"new story ready!";
note right: Profile Picker pill  •  shipped

' ---- Act 6: Read & rate ----
|Child|
:Open my Library
(Continue Reading + shelf);
note right: /library/:profileId  •  shipped
:Read passages,
make choices;
note right: /read/...  (Reader)  •  shipped
if (Online?) then (yes)
  :Progress saves as I go;
else (offline)
  :Read from cache,
  progress waits in a queue;
  note right: offline-first  •  shipped
  :On reconnect it syncs
  (reconcile if it clashes);
  note right: seq-offline / seq-reading-state
endif
:Reach an ending;
:Rate the story
(tap stars on the library shelf);
note right: shipped\n(rating lives on the library BookCard,\nnot the reader ending screen)

repeat while (Want another story?) is (yes) not (no)
|Child|
stop

legend bottom
  == Reading the journey ==
  Columns = who is acting: <b>Child</b>, <b>Guardian</b>, <b>Admin</b>, <b>System</b> (behind the scenes).
  |= Node |= Meaning |
  |<back:#FFFDF8>  white  </back>| Shipped in the app today |
  |<back:#F3D9D4>  rose   </back>| Planned target-state step, not yet built |
  The child-initiated request (Act 2, WS-B) is shipped: a guardian or admin
  approves or declines it from /guardian/requests. A guardian can also
  author a request directly from Intake without a prior child ask. Approval
  of the generated storybook (ADR-005) remains the one mandatory admin gate
  before any story reaches a child.
  ADR-014 (device-authorized kid access): Act 1's guardian sign-in is now
  conditional -- an already-authorized device skips it entirely for the
  Kids door. The former per-page parental gate collapsed into a single
  AdultGate at the root of the adult subtree: crossing UP from kid mode
  re-demands the password; guardian<->guardian, guardian<->admin, and
  admin<->guardian navigation is free once warm. See seq-device-grant.svg
  for the mint/verify/revoke mechanics.
endlegend

@enduml
